    "experimental_data": {
        "key_results": "Higher polymer concentration (039_F1) resulted in slower drug release, higher hardness, lower friability, and higher MDT. All formulations followed Higuchi release kinetics. Drug release was diffusion-dominated. Statistically significant differences (P<0.05) were found among drug release profiles.",
        "performance_metrics": "039_F1 was identified as the best formulation for sustained release, with a t75% of 7.93 hours and MDT of 3.44 hours. All tablets met USP specifications for weight variation and drug content (100±5%).",
        "statistical_analysis": "Statistically significant differences (P<0.05) were found among the drug release profiles from different polymeric matrices. Regression co-efficients (R²) were used to determine the best-fit kinetic model. Relative standard deviation (RSD) for UV method precision was 1.04%.",
